I found a solution:

    repeat{
      results = ((distance(site.by.species[sample(nrow(site.by.species)),],method=&#39;jaccard&#39;)&lt;=jaccard.similarity)*1) + results
       print(results[1,1])
       if (results[1,1] == 100){
         print(&quot;repeat loop ends&quot;);
         break
       }
    }

I used the repeat function here because I was only looking to output a single matrix rather than all of the matrices together as an array which is what I was getting with the `replicate()` method. My `repeat` ends once the `results[1,1]` hits 100 because this element in the matrix is the similarity of the same site which will always be equal to the `jaccard.similarity` table ([2,2];[3,3];and so on would also work), so each run adds 1 to this column.

There are probably much easier ways to do this!

